script: bundle exec rake syntax lint metadata_lint check:symlinks check:git_ignore check:dot_underscore check:test_file rubocop

Metrics/LineLength.Description: People have wide screens, use them.

GetText/DecorateString.Description: We don't want to decorate test output.

RSpec/BeforeAfterAll.Description: Beware of using after(:all) as it may cause state to leak between tests. A necessary evil in acceptance testing.

RSpec/HookArgument.Description: Prefer explicit :each argument, matching existing module's style

Style/BlockDelimiters.Description: Prefer braces for chaining. Mostly an aesthetical choice. Better to be consistent then.

Style/ClassAndModuleChildren.Description: Compact style reduces the required amount of indentation.

Style/EmptyElse.Description: Enforce against empty else clauses, but allow `nil` for clarity.

Style/FormatString.Description: Following the main puppet project's style, prefer the % format format.

Style/FormatStringToken.Description: Following the main puppet project's style, prefer the simpler template tokens over annotated ones.

Style/Lambda.Description: Prefer the keyword for easier discoverability.

Style/TernaryParentheses.Description: Checks for use of parentheses around ternary conditions. Enforce parentheses on complex expressions for better readability, but seriously consider breaking it up.

Style/TrailingCommaInArguments.Description: Prefer always trailing comma on multiline argument lists. This makes diffs, and re-ordering nicer.

Style/TrailingCommaInLiteral.Description: Prefer always trailing comma on multiline literals. This makes diffs, and re-ordering nicer.

Style/SymbolArray.Description: Using percent style obscures symbolic intent of array's contents.

matrix.CHECK: syntax lint metadata_lint check:symlinks check:git_ignore check:dot_underscore check:test_file rubocop

install: if ! $NOINSTALLEDCONSTRAINTS; then for pkg in $($HCPKG list --simple-output); do echo $pkg  | grep -vw -- language-puppet | sed 's/^/constraints: /' | sed 's/-[^-]*$/ installed/' >> cabal.project.local; done; fi
script: if ! $NOINSTALLEDCONSTRAINTS; then for pkg in $($HCPKG list --simple-output); do echo $pkg  | grep -vw -- language-puppet | sed 's/^/constraints: /' | sed 's/-[^-]*$/ installed/' >> cabal.project.local; done; fi
if [ "x$TEST" = "x--enable-tests" ]; then cabal new-test -w ${HC} ${TEST} ${BENCH} all; fi
if $HADDOCK; then cabal new-haddock -w ${HC} ${TEST} ${BENCH} all; else echo "Skipping haddock generation";fi
if $UNCONSTRAINED; then rm -f cabal.project.local; echo cabal new-build -w ${HC} --disable-tests --disable-benchmarks all; else echo "Not building without installed constraints"; fi

crayfishx/puppet-firewalld\\.travis.yml.script: bundle exec rake test SPEC_OPTS='--format documentation'

after_success:
if [ "$BUILD_LEADER" = "YES" ]; then
  if [ "$BUILD_AGGREGATE_STATUS" = "others_succeeded" ]; then
    echo "All Succeded! PUBLISHING..."
    export SAFE_TO_DEPLOY="true"
  else
    echo "Some Failed"
  fi
fi
after_failure:
if [ "$BUILD_LEADER" = "YES" ]; then
  if [ "$BUILD_AGGREGATE_STATUS" = "others_failed" ]; then
    echo "All Failed"
  else
    echo "Some Failed"
  fi
fi
